All bleeding is reduced by two categories. All First aid checks made to aid the character are at +50.

At 2 points: Psychological addiction to alcohol. When given an opportunity to get a drink, the character must roll a WIL check to avoid doing so. Each “drink” is assumed to give -5 AC penalty and the character may re-roll the WIL check after each drink. After the character stops drinking, the penalty is recovered at +5 per two hours (or +5 per hour if sleeping).
OR
Mild physical addiction to nicotine or caffeine (or a similar substance). If the substance is not available, penalty will increase gradually -5 AC per three hours, up to -15 AC and -1 I. The penalty is recovered at +10 AC per hour when the character takes the substance again.
No losses are suffered when the character sleeps.

-15 to the Endurance skill. Recover AC penalty due to tiring 3 points per hour of rest or 0 points per hour of light activity.
